CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 13, 1954, pg. 11 reads: "Daughters Of Isis - Sahara Court No. 9, Daughters of Isis, sponsored an oriental tea, Feb. 28, at Kay Club, and the members appeared in beautiful costumes befitting the occasion. Wendel Wray was the speaker.  Daughter Virginia M. Valentine is Illustrious Commandress; Daughter Ora Dee Highsmith was chairman, and Daughter Fannie Maynor, co-chairman.  Pictured here are Daughters Ora Dee Highsmith, Alberta Finch, Fannie Maynor, Gertrude Menton, Natalie Green, Mattie Blackwell, Leafie V. White, Cora Moon, Laura Poyner, Kathryn Gibson, Ida M. Dempsey, Lila Gilmore, Cora Finch, Hazel Roberts, Marcella Young, Eula Scales and Virginia Valentine, Illustrious Commandress."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Daughters of Isis, Sahara Court No. 9 members, including Ora Dee Highsmith, Alberta Finch, Fannie Maynor, Gertrude Menton, Natalie Green, Mattie Blackwell, Leafie V. Dempsey, Lila Gilmore, Cora Finch, Hazel Roberts, Marcella Young, Eula Scales and Virginia Valentine, seated second from right, posed in Kay Boys Club for Oriental Tea
